What you need to know:  The match, which will mark the start of the women’s handball contest at the delayed championships will take place at UCS Sede – Multi sport gym from 12pm Brazilian time (8pm in Kenya)The national women’s Deaf handball team will be hoping for a bright start against Turkey, as they look to shake off the underdogs tagAfter their clash with Turkey, Kenya will rest for one day before taking on champions Denmark at the same venue on May 3